@startuml flow_instance_closed
!theme plain
skinparam defaultFontName monospaced

title User Flow — Server Instance Closed (Redis Cross-Instance Signaling)

participant "Client A" as clientA
participant "Instance 1\nSignalingHandler" as inst1
participant "Redis\n(pub/sub + peer data)" as redis
participant "Instance 2\nRedisSignalingListener" as redisSub2
participant "Instance 2\nSignalingHandler" as inst2
participant "Client B\n(same user as A)" as clientB
participant "Client C\n(different user)" as clientC

note over inst1, inst2
  Normal state:
    Instance 1 → serves Client A
    Instance 2 → serves Client B (same user), Client C (different user)
  Both instances share one Redis.
end note

== Playback State Broadcast (cross-instance) ==

clientA -> inst1: PUT /playback
inst1 -> inst1: PlaybackStateService.saveState()\n→ persist to DB
inst1 -> redis: PUBLISH signaling:playback\n{userId, state JSON}
redis -> redisSub2: deliver message
redisSub2 -> inst2: deliverPlaybackStateChangedLocally(userId, state)
inst2 -> clientB: WS PLAYBACK_STATE_CHANGED
note over inst2, clientC: Client C belongs to a\ndifferent user — not notified

== Library Sync Trigger (cross-instance) ==

clientA -> inst1: POST /sync (library upload/change)
inst1 -> inst1: DataSyncService.performSync()\n→ apply changes to DB
inst1 -> redis: PUBLISH signaling:sync\n{userId}
redis -> redisSub2: deliver message
redisSub2 -> inst2: deliverSyncTriggerLocally(userId)
inst2 -> clientB: WS SYNC_TRIGGER
clientB -> inst2: POST /sync (pulls latest)

== WebRTC Signaling Across Instances ==

clientA -> inst1: WS OFFER {targetId: peerB}
inst1 -> inst1: routeToTarget(peerB)\n→ peerB not in local peerIndex
inst1 -> redis: PUBLISH signaling:webrtc\n{type:OFFER, targetId:peerB, ...}
redis -> redisSub2: deliver message
redisSub2 -> inst2: routeToTargetLocally(peerB)
inst2 -> clientB: WS OFFER

clientB -> inst2: WS ANSWER {targetId: peerA}
inst2 -> inst2: routeToTarget(peerA)\n→ peerA not in local peerIndex
inst2 -> redis: PUBLISH signaling:webrtc\n{type:ANSWER, targetId:peerA, ...}
redis -> redisSub2: deliver on Instance 1 side
note over inst1: Instance 1's RedisSignalingListener\ndelivers ANSWER to Client A

== Instance 1 Goes Down ==

note over inst1: Instance 1 shuts down\n(crash, deploy, scale-in, etc.)

inst1 -> inst1: afterConnectionClosed()\nfor each active session
inst1 -> inst1: remove sessions from\nregistry / userIndex / peerIndex

inst1 -> redis: HDEL peer:chunks:{songId} peerA\n(PeerTrackingService cleanup,\nfor every song peerA had cached)
inst1 -> redis: DEL peer:songs:{peerA}

note over redis
  peerA's chunk entries removed from Redis.
  Instance 2 will no longer route P2P
  requests to peerA.
  Instance 2 and its clients are unaffected.
end note

== Client A Reconnects to Instance 2 ==

clientA -> inst2: WebSocket reconnect\n(no auto-reconnect — client must retry)
inst2 -> inst2: register session in\nregistry / userIndex / peerIndex

clientA -> inst2: WS REGISTER_CACHE {songId, cachedIndices}
inst2 -> inst2: PeerTrackingService\n.registerPeerChunks()
inst2 -> redis: HSET peer:chunks:{songId}\npeerA → [cachedIndices]
inst2 -> redis: SADD peer:songs:{peerA} songId

note over redis
  peerA's chunk cache is restored.
  Next DISCOVER_PEERS for this song
  will include peerA again.
end note

@enduml